        "details": {
            "description": "<p>Ghostly smoke rising from an alchemical engine belches forth; the screeching sound of grinding gears echoes from the engine as it shutters to life.</p>",
            "disable": "<p>@Check[type:religion|dc:22|name:Eject the animating spirit|traits:hazard,haunt,complex] (trained) or @Check[type:engineering|dc:20|name:Eject the animating spirit|traits:hazard,haunt,complex] Lore (trained) to eject the animating spirit from its mechanical shell. Creatures gain a +2 circumstance bonus on their check if they use the airship's name, Harpy's Kiss, as part of their skill check, or a +4 circumstance bonus if they utter the name \"Phera Wyndslow.\" The haunt remains active until its spirit is ejected, the haunt is destroyed, or there are no living creatures within 30 feet.</p>",
            "isComplex": true,
            "level": {
                "value": 3
            },
            "reset": "<p>The haunt deactivates and resets after 1 hour.</p>",
